ZH: 他的天性就是喜欢孤独。
EN: His nature is to enjoy solitude.

ZH: 她天性温和善良。
EN: She has a gentle and kind nature.

ZH: 我们天性不同，所以经常发生分歧。
EN: We have different natures, so we often have disagreements.

ZH: 她的天性使她成为一名优秀的领导者。
EN: Her nature makes her an excellent leader.

ZH: 孩子们天性活泼好动。
EN: Children have a naturally lively and active nature.

ZH: 他的天性让他容易兴奋。
EN: His nature makes him easily excited.

ZH: 天性决定一个人会选择什么样的事业。
EN: Nature determines what kind of career a person will choose.

ZH: 她的天性让她喜欢旅行和探险。
EN: Her nature makes her enjoy traveling and exploring.

ZH: 他的天性是喜欢帮助别人。
EN: His nature is to enjoy helping others.

ZH: 天性使得自然界和谐起来。
EN: Nature makes the natural world harmonious.

ZH: 我相信人的天性是善良的。
EN: I believe that human nature is inherently good.

ZH: 你的天性决定你会成为怎样的人。
EN: Your nature determines what kind of person you will become.

ZH: 天性让人们与动物相互依存。
EN: Nature makes people mutually dependent with animals.

ZH: 每个人都有自己的天性，无法改变。
EN: Everyone has their own nature that cannot be changed.

ZH: 她的天性促使她积极参加社会活动。
EN: Her nature urges her to actively participate in social activities.

ZH: 天性使得植物和动物在生态系统中保持平衡。
EN: Nature maintains balance between plants and animals in the ecosystem.

ZH: 我的天性让我喜欢安静的环境。
EN: My nature makes me enjoy a quiet environment.

ZH: 人类的天性让他们对新事物充满好奇。
EN: It is human nature to be curious about new things.

ZH: 天性使得火山不断地喷发。
EN: Nature causes volcanoes to constantly erupt.

ZH: 年轻人的天性让他们寻找自己的个性。
EN: The nature of young people leads them to search for their own personalities.
